<section class="w3l-text-6 py-5" id="about">
    <div class="text-6-mian py-lg-5 py-md-4">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row top-cont-grid align-items-center">
                <div class="col-lg-6 left-img pr-lg-4">
                    <img src="~/images/PlaywriteOT/about-playwriteOT.jpg" alt="" class="img-responsive radius-image img-fluid" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 text-6-info mt-lg-0 mt-md-5 mt-4">
                    <h3 class="title-big mw-100">About Playwrite Occupational Therapy</h3>
                    <p class="mt-md-4 mt-3">
                        History of how Playwrite OT came into existence
                        Playwrite Occupational Therapy was opened in 2018 by Amy van Schoor our practice manager who has over a decade of experience , moved to Hillcrest leading Amy to open Playwrite OT but with the
                        aim of providing a space for families to feel safe and somewhere that children could grow to their full potential, Amy has 9 years alone on private practise but opened Playwrite OT
                        with the goal of providing outreach to communities unable to recieve quality care from a occupational therapy clinic.
                    </p>
                    <p class="mt-md-4 mt-3">
                        <h3>How does occupational therapy work?</h3>
                        Occupational therapists help with barriers that affect a person's emotional, social,and physical needs.
                        To do this, they use everyday activities, exercises, and other therapies. Occupational therapy helps kids play,
                        improves their school performance, and aids their daily activities, Playwrite Occupational therapy focuses on helping children develop and
                        learn through play.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
